The oral disc is anteroventral, with a single row of rounded marginal papillae below, with extra papillae laterally. The rostral gap in the papillae extends across the whole labium. The labial tooth row formula (
Altig 1970
) is 2/1. The upper and lower jaw sheaths are deeply pigmented for more than half of their height. Both jaw sheaths are finely serrated. The external nares are closer to the eye than the tip of the snout. Rostronasal distance/ orbitonasal distance = 1.5. The narial aperture is circular without a distinct margin. No narial valve is apparent. Internarial ratio: width of nostril/internarial distance = 0.15. There is no orbitonasal line. No pineal spot is present. The spiracle opening is small, elliptical, slightly away from the body, and is visible dorsally. The opening is dorsolateral.
